=====================================================
                     Geomys
       A Gopher Browser for Macintosh
                   Version 0.9.0
=====================================================

Browse Gopherspace from your classic Macintosh.


About Geomys
-----------

Geomys is a Gopher protocol browser for the Apple
Macintosh Plus and later models running System 6.0.8
or later. It connects to Gopher servers over TCP/IP
using MacTCP, providing a graphical browser interface
for navigating Gopherspace.

Geomys implements RFC 1436 (The Internet Gopher
Protocol) and RFC 4266 (The gopher URI Scheme).
All 18 canonical and non-canonical Gopher item types
are fully supported, including directories, text
files, search queries, binary file downloads, image
save with metadata, and HTML URL extraction.

The browser features a web-style interface with an
address bar, back/forward/home buttons, a combined
stop/go/refresh action button, and a status bar --
all designed to follow the Apple Human Interface
Guidelines.


Features
--------

  - Multi-window browsing with up to 4 simultaneous
    Gopher windows and background loading
  - Binary file downloads to disk via SFPutFile
    with progress dialog and Stop button
  - Image save with GIF/PNG format detection and
    dimension display
  - HTML URL extraction with copyable dialog
  - Go menu: Back, Forward, Home, Refresh, Stop,
    Open Location, and browsing history
  - Dynamic stop/go/refresh button right of address
    bar that changes based on browser state
  - Status bar hover hints showing URIs and file info
  - Download-specific visual indicators: angle bracket
    labels and distinct theme colors
  - 9 color themes including Light, Dark, Solarized,
    Tokyo Night, Green Screen, Classic, Platinum
  - Find in Page (Cmd-F) with Find Again (Cmd-G)
  - Print support (Cmd-P) via Printing Manager
  - Text selection and copy to clipboard (Cmd-C)
  - Keyboard link navigation with Up/Down arrows
  - Save Page As (Cmd-S) for text and directory pages
  - CP437 character set and Unicode glyph rendering
  - Local page cache for instant back/forward
  - Gopher+ protocol support
  - MacTCP pre-loaded at startup for fast first connect
  - Dynamic directory capacity up to 2,000 items
  - Page styles: Traditional, Plain, Markdown
  - Font selection: Chicago, Monaco, Courier, Geneva


System Requirements
-------------------

  - Macintosh Plus or later (68000 CPU)
  - System 6.0.8 or later
  - MacTCP 2.1 (configured with a valid TCP/IP
    connection)
  - 4 MB RAM recommended
  - Network connection (Ethernet or compatible)

Color themes require Mac II or later with Color
QuickDraw. Monochrome themes (Light, Dark) work
on all systems including Mac Plus.


Getting Started
---------------

1. Make sure MacTCP is installed and configured in
   your Control Panel. You will need a working TCP/IP
   connection to your network.

2. Double-click the Geomys application to launch it.

3. Geomys opens to a blank page. Set your home page
   in Options > Home Page, or type a Gopher URL in
   the address bar and press Return.

4. Click on directory items to navigate. Click on
   text items to read them. Click on binary, image,
   or sound items to save them to disk.

5. Use the Back and Forward buttons (or Cmd-[ and
   Cmd-]) to navigate through your browsing history.

6. To select text, click and drag in the content
   area. Double-click to select a word. Hold Shift
   and click to extend the selection. Press Cmd-C
   to copy. The address bar also supports Cut,
   Copy, and Paste via the Edit menu.

7. Press Cmd-. to cancel an in-progress download
   or page load.

8. To quit, choose Quit from the File menu or press
   Command-Q.


Credits
-------

Geomys was created by Micheal Waltz with assistance
from Claude Code, an AI by Anthropic.

Geomys is cross-compiled on Linux using Retro68, the
68k Macintosh cross-compilation toolchain by
Wolfgang Thaller.

This project incorporates code from two open-source
classic Macintosh applications by joshua stein:

  wallops - IRC client for classic Macintosh
  MacTCP wrapper, DNS resolution, and utility
  functions are used directly from this project.

  subtext - BBS server for classic Macintosh
  Additional networking and utility code.

Both projects are released under the ISC license.

Geomys is a sibling project to Flynn, a Telnet and
Finger client for classic Macintosh. Both share
infrastructure and design patterns.


